Hi,

field contents indexed with Field.text are stored=20
verbatim in the index - thus, you can get back the=20
original text when you access it using stingValue().=20

This has nothing to do with how the text is=20
indexed, i.e., how it is tokenized and stored into
the index. You probably have a token "workers" and=20
one "howto", both pointing to this text (that's why=20
it is called an inverted index, the words point to
the text). Your analyzer does this tokenization
for you.

If you search using the query parser, you
can only do this on indexed fields, e.g.,
those indexed with Field.text or Field.UnStored.=20
If you store a text as a keyword,
you must construct a TermQuery and search
with it. Thus, you would actually get a
term ("title", "Workers HowTo").

Regards,

Karsten

-----Urspr=FCngliche Nachricht-----
