the command i gave you (i.e. java org.apache.lucene.demo.IndexHTML -c=
reate
-index \jakarta-tomcat-4.0.6\webapps\index .. from some sub-directory=
 of
webapps) should work, it did on my machine.   =20

as you can see from the above, you have to replace the {index-dir} in=
 the
command with the path to the index directory (without {} around it). =
=20

you can create a directory wherever you want (c:\lucene\index or what=
ever
and supply the full path (in place of {index-dir}) as \lucene\index) =
and as
long as the user that is running tomcat has read and write permission=
 for
that directory, tomcat will be able to read and write to it.



=20
